Hi this one have an easy setup 
1.-copy conky folder to your home like this /home/you/conky
2.- copy and paste "aptup"  in /etc/cron.hourly/
	sudo cp $HOME/conky/aptud /etc/cron.hourly
2(a).- make it executable 
 	$ sudo chmod +x /etc/cron.hourly/aptup
2(b).-  restart cron 
	$ sudo /etc/init.d/cron restart
3.-make executable "conky-updates.pl" it's in /openbox/scripts/
	$ chmod $HOME/conky/openbox/scripts/conky-updates.pl
4.-copy the font to ~/.fonts and update your cache
	$ sudo fc-cache -fv
5.-make executable "start" file and execute it 
6.- enjoy XD
optional If you use tint2 copy  "tint2rc" to ~/.config/tint2
